Subject: [PATCH] tty: hvc: fix buffer overflow during hvc_alloc().
References: bnc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 5.6.8
Git-commit: 9a9fc42b86c06120744555fea43fdcabe297c656

commit 9a9fc42b86c06120744555fea43fdcabe297c656 upstream.

If there is a lot(more then 16) of virtio-console devices
or virtio_console module is reloaded
- buffers 'vtermnos' and 'cons_ops' are overflowed.
In older kernels it overruns spinlock which leads to kernel freezing:
https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1786239

To reproduce the issue, you can try simple script that
loads/unloads module. Something like this:
while [ 1 ]
do
  modprobe virtio_console
  sleep 2
  modprobe -r virtio_console
  sleep 2
done

